<!DOCTYPE html>
<html dir="ltr" lang="en-US">
<% include ./partials/head %>

<body style="">
  <script>
    window.fbAsyncInit = function() {
      FB.init({
        appId      : '<%- process.env.FACEBOOK_APP_ID %>',
        xfbml      : true,
        version    : 'v2.6'
      });
    };

    (function(d, s, id){
       var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];
       if (d.getElementById(id)) {return;}
       js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id;
       js.src = "//connect.facebook.net/en_US/sdk.js";
       fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs);
     }(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));
  </script>

<div class="container-fluid" style="text-align:center;color:white; background-color:#3A539B;">
    <div class="header">
          <div class="row">
              <div style="height:50px;"></div>
              <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-4">
                <a href="/">  <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/aws-website-portfoliosite-bf6tr/patron-messenger-short-header.png" class="img-responsive"></img></a>

              </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">

              <h2 class="header-one">A Bar Reccomendation Bot</h2>
              <p class="text"> Serving up great spots with mellow beats for friends and lovers. <br> Built by Alexander Green. </p>



              </div>

              <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-4">
                <div style="height:50px;"></div>
                <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/aws-website-portfoliosite-bf6tr/iphone-patron.png" style="width:80%;"></img>
                <div style="height:50px;"></div>
                <h2 class="header-one"> This one's on the house. </h2>
                <hr style="width:50%;">
                <p class="text"> Hit the link to try out Patron - no work necessary. </p>
                <br>
                <div class="fb-send-to-messenger"
                  messenger_app_id="<%- process.env.FACEBOOK_APP_ID %>"
                  page_id="<%- process.env.FACEBOOK_PAGE_ID %>"
                  data-ref="PASS_THROUGH_PARAM"
                  color="white"
                  size="large" style="margin:auto;"></div>


              </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row">
            <div style="height:100px;"></div>
            <div class="col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-3">
              <div style="height:50px;"></div>
              <h2 class="header-one"> Search by borough.</h2>
                    <hr style="width:50%;">
              <p class="text"> Try Brooklyn, Queens, Manhattan, and Long Island. That's right - I hate Staten Island so much we went with Nassau County first. Scandalous.  </p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-3">
              <img class="img-responsive" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/patron-bars/gifs/patron-bar-search-borough.gif"></img>

            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="row">
            <div style="height:150px;"></div>

            <div class="col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-3">
              <h2 class="header-one visible-xs"> Search by price.</h2>
                <hr style="width:50%;" class="visible-xs">
              <p class="text visible-xs"> Try a price range (from 1 to 5, cheap to expensive). Cheers to all the dive bars out there. </p>

              <img class="img-responsive" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/patron-bars/gifs/patron-bar-search-price.gif"></img>

            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-3">
              <div style="height:50px;"></div>
              <h2 class="header-one hidden-xs"> Search by price.</h2>
                    <hr style="width:50%;" class="hidden-xs">
              <p class="text hidden-xs"> Try a price range (from 1 to 5, cheap to expensive). Cheers to all the dive bars out there. </p>
            </div>


          </div>

          <div class="row">
            <div style="height:150px;"></div>
            <div class="col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-3">
              <div style="height:50px;"></div>
              <h2 class="header-one"> Search by type.</h2>
              <hr style="width:50%;">
              <p class="text"> Find what you're looking for.  <br>
              These are the five ways you can search: <br>
            <ul class="text">
            <li> college bar </li>
            <li> dive bar </li>
            <li> chill </li>
            <li> dancing </li>
            <li> date spot </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-3">
              <img class="img-responsive" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/patron-bars/gifs/patron-bar-search-type.gif"></img>

            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="row">
            <div style="height:50px;"></div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
              <div style="height:50px;"></div>
              <h2 class="header-one"> Why'd you build this?</h2>
              <hr style="width:50%;">
              <p class="text">
                Every month this year I want to challenge myself with a new project.
                Nothing big, nothing sexy, but small concepts I've always wanted to try.
                This one's a Facebook Messenger bot. Next up is an Alexa Skill.
                <br>
                <br>
                Here's what I'd like to add - entering multiple parameters for search, more refined search by neighborhood in the city, a streamlined way to upload new bars, and maybe a few other tweaks along the way.
                <br>
                  <div class="fb-like" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/Patron-NYC-362819280749662/" data-layout="button_count" data-action="like" data-size="small" data-show-faces="false" data-share="true"></div>
              </p>
            </div>



          </div>
